{
  "texts": [
    "Singlestage detection methods, such as SSD (Elgendy, 2020) and the YOLO series, predict an object's approximate bounding box in a single neural network run, enabling quick and effective object recognition.",
    "Although this comes at the expense of lower accuracy rates, these methods demonstrate excellent reliability compared to two-stage detectors.",
    "Typically, greater accuracy is achieved in identifying larger items compared to smaller and closely spaced objects.",
    "Later iterations of YOLO (Redmon et al., 2016), such as YOLOv2 (Redmon and Farhadi, 2017), YOLOv3 (Redmon and Farhadi, 2018), and others, have successfully incorporated deeper neural networks to enhance performance.",
    "This modification has yielded more effective results while maintaining strong accuracy and low processing complexity."
  ]
}